### Spring Boot + Liquibase API Tests

# Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health

### 1. Get All Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users

### 2. Get Active Users Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/active

### 3. Get User by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1

### 4. Get User by Username
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/username/admin

### 5. Create New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "john_doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "securepass123",
  "phone": "1234567890",
  "address": "123 Main Street, City"
}

### 6. Create User - Validation Error (Short Username)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "ab",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 7. Create User - Validation Error (Invalid Email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 8. Create User - Validation Error (Short Password)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "12345"
}

### 9. Update User
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "admin_updated",
  "email": "admin.updated@example.com",
  "password": "newadminpass123",
  "phone": "9999999999",
  "address": "456 Updated Street, New City"
}

### 10. Update User - Partial Update (Keep Password)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "admin",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "",
  "phone": "1111111111",
  "address": "789 Partial Street"
}

### 11. Delete User
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/4

### 12. Disable User
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1/disable

### 13. Enable User
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1/enable

### 14. Record Login (Update Last Login)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1/login

### 15. Get Non-Existent User (404 Error)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/99999

### 16. Create Duplicate User (409 Conflict)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "admin",
  "email": "another@admin.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### H2 Console Access
# Open in browser: http://localhost:8080/h2-console
# JDBC URL: jdbc:h2:mem:testdb
# Username: sa
# Password: (leave empty)

### Check Liquibase Changesets
# Liquibase tables are created automatically:
# - DATABASECHANGELOG: Tracks executed changesets
# - DATABASECHANGELOGLOCK: Prevents concurrent migrations

# Query to see Liquibase history in H2:
# SELECT * FROM DATABASECHANGELOG ORDER BY DATEEXECUTED;
